 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Buyer ANDURIL INDUSTRIES Irvine, CA Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Anduril is a defense technology company, bringing Silicon Valley talent and funding to the defense sector. Our technology helps our customers solve their toughest challenges by enabling them to make better, more informed decisions in life-and-death situations. Weâ€™ve assembled a diverse team of experts in artificial intelligence, computer vision, sensor fusion, optics, and data analysis that are creating software and hardware solutions to radically evolve the capabilities of the United States and our allies. If you are passionate about solving problems that have real impact, come join Anduril and build the future of defense. 
Anduril Supply Chain is seeking a Buyer to join our team. The Supply Chain team works closely with engineering, finance, and manufacturing to ensure parts that compose our revolutionary products arrive with good quality, on time, and at a fair cost. 
 
 As Buyer, you will source production components and manage a Bill of Materials (BOM) for several teams. The right person for this role has purchasing experience in a manufacturing environment, is able to read blueprints/drawings, and is comfortable with ERP/PLM/MRP/MES systems. If you are someone who enjoys launching new products, influencing component selection, and owning a project from cradle-to-grave then this is the role for you. 
 What you'll do: 
Develop and implement sourcing strategy for direct commodities and/or categories.
 Issue purchase orders for production parts using a Bill of Materials (BOM).
 Mitigate supply risk, documenting and reporting supplier performance. 
Serve as internal product expert, providing sourcing recommendations for critical components. 
Support continuous improvement initiatives for cost savings, quality improvement, and on-time delivery.
 Maintain strong supplier relationships.
 Own the procurement process from cradle to grave. 
 Required Qualifications: 
3+ years technical procurement experience in a manufacturing environment. 
Excellent customer service skills.
 Experience working cross functionally.
 Strong analytical and organizational skills. 
Ability to read drawings and blueprints. 
 Preferred Qualifications: 
Experience sourcing electronic (PCB/PCBA) components 
Experience sourcing machined components 
